<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre># Send contents of file to command
$ command &lt; file	

# Redirect Stderr twice		
$ command 2&gt; file2 &gt; file1 2&gt;&amp;1	

# Text to Stdin (command)
$ command &lt;&lt; 'text'				

# Redirect both Stdout and Stderr to file
$ command &gt; file 2&gt;&amp;1		

# Redirect Stdout to one file and Stderr to another
$ command &gt; file1 2&gt; file2	

# Pipe Stdout and Stderr to another process	
$ command 2&gt;&amp;1 | command2			

$ less &lt;(gzip -cd foo.gz)
$ gzip -cd foo.gz &amp;&amp; less foo

# Redirect an error
$ echo An Error &gt;&amp;2 2&gt;&amp;1 | sed -e 's/A/I/'

# Duplicate output
$ command | tee file1 &gt; file2</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
<a href="http://puma.io/">Puma</a> and, to a lesser extent,
<a href="http://errtheblog.com/">Err the Blog</a>.</div></body></html>